Job Description Employee Help More Use tab to navigate through the menu Delivery Associate Job Description Pursuit Packages is excited to announce that we are now hiring drivers to join our delivery team in the greater Columbus area! JOB PERKS: $18.25 per hour for standard van drivers starting their first route 9:15 am start time! Opportunity to go home early and still get paid! $125 for a pair of Zappos work shoes Regular raises for top performers Paid Time Off Full Health, Dental & Vision Benefits (benefits for full time only) Fun opportunities for bonuses, cash and other prizes! Weekly gift cards, Buckeyes tickets, Switch, large screen TV, Playstation & much more! Employee Focused company - Opportunity to even WIN A FREE TRIP TO VEGAS! Full Time = rotating schedule of only 4 days Part time = same hour shift, but you can work as many or as few days per week as you want Managers are promoted from Opportunities to learn & grow! High quality and well maintained vehicles The open road is your no stuffy cubicles here! WHAT THE JOB IS: Physically Demanding! You won t need the gym on days you work! You will lift up to (assistive tools available), bend, reach, crouch, and climb stairs regularly Deliver large amounts of packages very quickly to many different locations Stops per day vary but usually average from - , so you will be climbing in and out of the van frequently You will be walking and climbing stairs frequently Fix any customer delivery issues or concerns that come Be professional while working Load and sort packages in the vehicle daily Responsible for cleanliness, safety, fuel level, and operating condition of delivery vehicle Responsible for safe operation and maneuvering of a large vehicle Train other teammates, assist with rescue routes Carry packages from vehicle to buildings in all weather conditions WHAT WE NEED: years of age or Valid driver s license Drug test required Must be able to effectively use a GPS and smart phone ​ Pursuit Packages LLC is an equal employment opportunity employer dedicated to establishing and maintaining a diverse Pursuit Packages, LLC does not discriminate on the basis of age, gender, race, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, pregnancy, religion, veteran status, political affiliation, disability, labor organization membership status, or other Interested? through a comedy club and educational The Crow , a Santa Monica Comedy Collaborative, is a safe space for all to laugh, learn, and evolve as humans through comedy, writing and the performing The Crow is for ALL AGES, ABILITIES, GENDERS, BIPOC, LGBTQIA2S+ humans performing, studying, and (There are separate shows and family ) The art of comedy will provide a platform for expression, healing, and social CROW stands for Comedy Reflects Our World , and we will achieve this by partnering with our local community to share our passion for the art and using it for good, levity and social Our Company Culture : We strive for constant growth and Our duty is to create an environment that allows development for Our priority is building and nurturing relationships between seasoned creatives and novice Our passion is helping foster professional growth in the comedy But like, how is comedy something that can help social progress? Thanks for asking! We believe that creating a rich, bright and eclectic comedy culture will foster the sharing of different We are curious about other’s points of When we laugh about the human experience, and discover different ways to process the world, we can heal and come Check out the Crow’s What do you see? A crow’s body? A crow’s head? Change the way you look at things, and you will be able to understand others and see that our differences can bring us Let us be the wind beneath your J K. Just let us build you a stage that is Cool? Rather than being one or the other, lead generation is a part of both sales and While most leads are generated through a form of marketing, they are generated to help drive sales and increase business Unfortunately, in some situations, there can be mild hostility and tension between the sales and marketing teams within a This is often tied to a crossover of roles and responsibilities, disagreement of methods, a lack of communication, or unaligned To create an effective lead generation process from start to finish, sales and marketing need to work together in harmony rather than frequently clashing with one When creating a lead generation strategy that brings together your sales and marketing teams, you need to develop a clearly laid out, and easily understandable process that both teams can use to effectively work This process should include: A clearly mapped out document explaining which teams and individuals hold specific roles and A clear and quick method of communication that both teams can A clear understanding of when information needs to be shared discussed between departments and the individuals who should be addressed in each An effective lead generation strategy should be able to segment sales and marketing whilst simultaneously bringing them This can take a good amount of work to get right, but when done correctly your process for generating new business will be far smoother and more Why is Lead Generation Important for a Business? Lead generation is a vital part of generating new business opportunities and growing your Without some form of lead generation, your business can often struggle to keep up with those competitors who are regularly engaging with potential For some businesses, gaining new customers may not require a great deal of effort, especially if their offering is filling a large gap in the market, is of a high quality and has little Other businesses, however, will have to develop and maintain a consistent lead generation strategy to stay ahead of the Besides keeping up a steady stream of new business and beating the competition, lead generation allows businesses to keep in contact with their audience, build brand awareness, and build a database of prospects and potential It also helps to map out the landscape of the market, and when done correctly can provide value to both the client and the What Is The Value Of Outsourcing Lead Generation? There are many benefits to outsourced lead generation and it ultimately begins with It’s the cost related to salaries and benefits in addition to burden and expense associated with recruiting, hiring and Managerial time should also be taken into account, as should the time it will take to build, train and maintain an inside team (that will likely have high turnover). Just as you’re an expert at what you do, B2B lead generation companies are experts at what they They follow the best practices based on proven results to produce the highest possible ROI for the time spent on Why Is Lead Generation Important? Lasting success often requires more than setting up a shop and hoping customers find your Lead generation streamlines the sales process by targeting interested buyers and feeding them through a proven appointment setting Without lead generation services in your arsenal, you could miss crucial opportunities to grow your Not only are B2B lead generation services valuable to your bu

July , By Ramsay Crooks Earlier this week I pointed out Googleâs recent embrace of user experience (UX) in the form of their new Core Web Vitals and how these metrics will be added to the organic search ranking algorithm in the coming Today, Iâd like to break down aspects ofÂ their multiple articles on the topic for easier reading and to contextualize things from a UX point of viewâ¦Â Why should I care? Â Well, due to the huge importance of UX, Google is now telling us to pay attention - and attempting to help us do âEarlier this month, the Chrome team announced Core Web Vitals , a set of metrics related to speed, responsiveness and visual stability, to help site owners measure user experience on the  Obviously UX matters so why is this different? As Google puts it, â We will introduce a new signal that combines Core Web Vitals with our existing signals for page experience to provide a holistic picture of the quality of a userâs experience on a web  This is notable in that Core Web Vitals are being considered by Google as (SEO ranking) signals for organic This means user experience improvements are still great for converting existing AND they now also help to acquire said traffic in the first place by being a positive signal for organic rankings (SEO). And Google thinks this will have tangible business âWe believe this will contribute to business success on the web as users grow more engaged and can transact with less friction  We agree wholeheartedly! Less friction is a good thing (unless youâre a tire - and itâs raining).Â It seems Google is in this for the long I guess this UX thing isnât just a fadâ¦ â...we plan to incorporate more page experience signals on a yearly basis to both further align with evolving user expectations and increase the aspects of user experience that we can  Furthermore, a broad based tool kit to help developers, product teams, and marketers to make continual improvements shows that Google sees UX as critical to the future of quality search âTo help out, weâve updated popular developer tools such as Lighthouse and PageSpeed Insights to surface Core Web Vitals information and recommendations, and Google Search Console provides a dedicated report to help site owners quickly identify opportunities for Weâre also working with external tool developers to bring Core Web Vitals into their  What is Google Measuring? The finer details and some nerdiness on what Google is looking at: Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) : Measures loading To provide a good user experience, sites should strive to have LCP occur within the first seconds of the page starting to First Input Delay (FID) : Measures To provide a good user experience, sites should strive to have an FID of less than milliseconds . Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) : Measures visual To provide a good user experience, sites should strive to have a CLS score of less than . In other words, three things: Page load speed The snappiness of interactions on the site (when you click or tap, how long does it take for something to happen?) The visual stability of the page itself (are , , and ad units making it hard to read content, click and tap links or buttons, or navigate in general?) Along with additional page experience ranking factors including , , , and intrusive interstitial guidelines , the UX signals that Google can measure as a bot crawling your site form a basic foundational approach for the machine to build UX into its ranking While the metrics that Googleâs "algo" and their new tools measure are a great start to understanding how to improve user experience, they donât tell the entire There are additional tools and tactics to help suss out specific user frustration and friction issues (the qualitative âwhyâ), as well as propose the hypotheses (and a b n testing roadmap) to achieve the right page experience changes for your users (the actionable ânow whatâ). So Youâre Saying I Need UX Optimization AND SEO to Rank Better in Google? Yes and This incorporation of UX signals is not an ranking factor (afterall, there are hundreds), but it can be a difference â...In cases where there are multiple pages that have similar content, page experience becomes much more important for visibility in  And there are big reasons to focus on UX beyond jumping a few spots on your competitorsÂ in the organic As Google puts it, âWe believe user engagement will improve as experiences on the web get better -- and that by incorporating these new signals into Search, we ll help make the web better for  By providing this overview of Core Web Vitals, Google hopes to â help the diverse ecosystem of web

Services – PARC Home Care Home About Us Services Contact Us Careers Home About Us Services Contact Us Careers Compassion At PARC Home Care we are dedicated to provide compassionate, quality care in the comfort of your Skilled services Skilled medical home care services are designed to treat individuals in the safety of their own Home care has been proven to result in optimal healing and recovery from illness or By establishing in home care services, patients can shorten their stay in hospitals and other acute care PARC Home Care’s staff of medical professionals works closely with your doctors and other health professionals to ensure that all clinical and medical needs are Our efficient referral and intake process ensures that a clinical staff member sees most patients within Skilled Nursing Our dedicated nurses manage patients’ injuries, illnesses and chronic conditions with services such as: Vital sign monitoring Wound Ostomy care Catheter care and Diabetes and Chronic heart failure Physical Therapy Our licensed therapists help patients restore mobility and increase their personal safety with: Fall prevention, Muscle , Orthopedic Joint replacement care Neurological care associated with Parkinson’s, MS and Occupational Therapy Our licensed therapists assist patients in restoring physical ability to remain independent with ADLs at home through: Exercises related to activities of daily living Functional upper body Fine motor dexterity Adaptive equipment and Splinting training and Transfer Speech Therapy Our credentialed therapists assess, diagnose, treat and help prevent speech and communication disorders through: Memory training, Cognitive therapy, Swallowing treatment, and Dysphagia Dysarthria. Additional Support Services To ensure that our patients have access to the important services and resources that complement their medical plan of care, we offer medical social workers, home health aides, registered dietitians, community resources, and translation services as Fall Prevention Program Falls are the leading cause of injury in adults over the age of Our clinicians that specialize in balance programs use practices and Fall Risk Assessment tools to tailor an individualized fall prevention program for each individual They are committed to helping patients stay safe in their homes and out of the Opioid Program Our team of nurses and physical therapists work closely with patients, and their families, referring physicians and pharmacists to determine how patients can receive the lowest effective medication dosage and identify alternate treatments to alleviate the patient’s pain with a focus on physical Patients best suited for this program are those who: Do not want to simply mask their pain those who believe the risk of opioid use outweighs the rewards and those who have pain or function problems related to low back pain, hip or knee osteoarthritis, or Fast Track Orthopedic Program Have your patients from their homes within one week into our brand new outpatient facility (Prevent Physical Therapy and Wellness). Enjoy the benefits of having the same PT follow you from your home into the Program Goals include: Transition patients to their homes in a safe manner Educate the patient and their family about precautions and guidelines related to surgery and their recovery Build patients’ joint range of motion, strength, balance and endurance Get patients back to being independent with transfers, bed mobility, stairs, and ambulation support Program Objectives: Nurses and therapists initiate services within hours of discharge from a hospital or inpatient rehabilitation facility Therapists assess patients’ safety and durable medical equipment for your home needs All programs are tailored to the physician surgeon protocols based on the type of surgery performed Therapists provide care to improve all functional outcomes for the patient to return to independence Skilled nurses assess with clinical status, including edema control, pain management, incision healing, and monitoring signs and symptoms of infection Skilled nurses and therapists work closely with our Opioid Program team to allow patients to safely discharge medications as appropriate Home health aides, social workers, and nutritionists are available as needed At PARC Home Care, we ensure that each patient is provided with utmost care and attention, allowing them to remain independent in their PARC Brochure Pages About Us Services Contact us Join our team contact us North Western STE West Bloomfield MI   About Us – PARC Home Care Home About Us Services Contact Us Careers Home About Us Services Contact Us Careers About PARC Home Care Independence through Care Jump to Services Our Mission To ensure that each patient is provided with utmost care and attention, allowing them to remain independent in their We believe this can be achieved through integrating medical advancements with constant PARC Home Care is led by healthcare professionals Our standards are focused

monitors, so we don’t have to stare into small little screens like our watches and phones, and also let us work where and when we want, without carrying bulky laptops or This future also brings with it not just information displays about the real world, but a new “Mirror World” (to borrow a term from a cover article in Wired Magazine) which will show us amazing new entertainment, teach us wonderous new things, help us at work, let us play with our friends in new ways, and present new ways of discovering retail experiences, not to mention products and This future is a major paradigm shift from where we are It’s the fourth shift of the personal computing age, one that promises to make computing far more personal than ever To get there we will see the development of many new companies and technologies, and that’s where Infinite Retina comes The people at Infinite Retina joined together around our love of And our curiosity about what makes companies succeed and Our team has been there at the start of many new companies and we have a deep rolodex of decision makers who build companies and share their products and services with the There is a perfect storm coming of spatial computing glasses, which bring VR and AR not just to businesses, but consumers, along with artificial intelligence, autonomous vehicles and innovation, that do many things better than humans All hitting in the next few As this storm hits, we’ll see many new ideas, products, services, and companies that need to be brought to market and find The people who are funding this storm are different than the ones who funded, say, Tesla or Airbnb or It also affects how entrepreneurs, developers, lawyers, PR people, recruiters, journalists, and influencers approach the Spatial Computing But we’ve studied this market deeply, written books, and built many relationships with people in the industry – all of which can be brought to bear on these new Spatial Computing projects and It’s an exciting None of us are wearing glasses or HMDs all day long Many Spatial Computing companies will be started over the next five Infinite Retina has the team to catalyze this new age of personal Kaua i Why Our Work Matters In The News Events & Opportunities Donate The Pulaski Story Edward Pulaski The Pulaski Story The Pulaski, our namesake and logo, is a half axe, half mattock It chops and cleaves, it excavates and grubs, it is the tool for countless Whether you have hefted one or not, odds are you have walked or ridden a trail that was shaped by For over a hundred years the pulaski has been the first tool reach for when constructing and maintaining new trails and the one tool you will always see firefighters carry into a Edward Pulaski, commonly known as ‘Big Ed’ was an iconic hero of the Big Burn He began working for the Coeur d’Alene National Forest in as a Forest Ranger, and in he directed hundreds of firefighters in daily activities outside of Wallace, Throughout his firefighting career he learned that being quick on one’s feet is of the utmost “ Dragging armfuls of tools around was not only impractical when fighting fires if it slowed you down, it might also kill Working in his backyard forge, Pulaski combined two of the most important axe and the mattock, a kind of lightweight ” Why Do We Use Traditional Tools? The majority of the work we complete is within Wilderness In , Congress passed the Wilderness Act in order to preserve and protect certain lands “in their natural condition” and thus “secure for present and future generations the benefits of ” One of the legal implications of federally designated wilderness management is that motorized transport and mechanized equipment are prohibited within wilderness What that means for us is that we primarily rely on the use of traditional tools including: crosscut saws, pulaskis, shovels, hand saws, and Proper use of these tools takes training and PUG volunteers are able to learn how and when to use these tools in order to complete our trail maintenance objectives safely and Pulaski Users Group is a (c)(3) Cash donations are tax Tax ID# Made with Squarespace   What We Do — Pulaski Users Group 0 Skip to Content Who We Are Who We Are The Pulaski Story Contact Our Approach What We Do What We ve Done Malama - Kaua i Why Our Work Matters In The News Events & Opportunities Donate Open Menu Close Menu Who We Are Who We Are The Pulaski Story Contact Our Approach What We Do What We ve Done Malama - Kaua i Why Our Work Matters In The News Events & Opportunities Donate Open Menu Close Menu Folder: Who We Are Back Who We Are The Pulaski Story Contact Folder: Our Approach Back What We Do What We ve Done Malama - Kaua i Why Our Work Matters In The News Events & Opportunities Donate What We Do Since , we have provided training, tools, and leadership for volunteer driven trail maintenance projects across central H
